dens in china 1984 1995 an empirical assessment it was presented at a june 2001 workshop on opportunities and constraints in china's rural transition a critical appraisal of two decades of reform and development held at the division of social science hong kong university of science and technology the paper will be revised but it currently provides one of the first estimations of the actual burdens that china's peasant had to bear from the late 1980s to the mid 1990s contact jean c oi events & presentations attempted assassinations protests and uncertainty taiwan's presidential election april 7 2004 special event jean c oi tom gold ramon myers larry diamond search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages research news shorenstein aparc titles bring new perspective to china's ongoing transformation and us rok relations march 4 2010 news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
